      "description": "The Bill of Rights (BoR) is in scaffold status with all six articles (I–VI) marked '[To be defined by human principal]'. The BoR is the mandatory compliance perimeter enforced by Arbiter (#190) at every scope query, and the Mission Statement Protocol (MSP) declares it the overarching constraint that trumps any MSP rule. Without defined articles, there is no bounded scope of enterprise, no list of prohibited activities, no core identity, and no reservation of human authority. The governance state slice is empty, confirming that no BoR amendment or human-principal sign-off has occurred. The system operates under default-permissive MSP evaluation, but the BoR gate is effectively non-functional, exposing the DIO to authorising actions outside any human-defined perimeter.",
